HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 497
By Hurt
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Jayden Garcia on his
receipt of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable citizens who have dedicated their time and energies to helping
others; and
WHEREAS, each year, 1.3 million Tennessee volunteers give over 99 million hours of
community service, contributing $2.6 billion to Tennessee's economy; and
WHEREAS, these volunteers are the backbone of our communities, and by donating
their time and talents to fulfill needs that would otherwise go unmet, they embody the spirit of
giving; and
WHEREAS, Jayden Garcia of Lauderdale County is one such exemplary person, who is
a recipient of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award in recognition of his laudable commitment
to his community; and
WHEREAS, the older brother of a child with Down syndrome, Mr. Garcia ensures his
sibling's safe drop-off and pick-up from school every day, and concerned about rising school
violence, he and his coaches created a program where members of the football team escort
elementary school students in and out of the building at arrival and dismissal; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his praiseworthy work with younger students, Mr. Garcia
generously volunteers his time to assist in local building projects around his hometown, and
utilizing his superlative leadership, he sets a model of civic and moral virtue for his fellow
teammates as the football team captain; and
WHEREAS, Jayden Garcia is a young man of sincere and abiding faith; his involvement
in Hope Church provides yet another facet to his outstanding achievements in altruism; and
